rComments: I learned so much in this course! Feedback was always helpful and available, the kind you'd be more likely to find in an even smaller class. Everything you needed to do to succeed was clearly laid out, plus guidance to explore if wanted. With everything online, attending a class that leaves you feeling more at ease or inspired is pretty great.
Professor Morrow is my favorite painting professor/teacher I have ever had, EVER. He is super interesting and incredibly talented.

Andrew Morrow is an okay prof. He is pretty generous grader however, when giving an assignment his guidelines are not very specific. He also does not give great feedback after giving back an assignment. His lessons and assignments are pretty basic. If you go to the class and hand in assignments you are pretty much guaranteed a pass.
Awesome prof- one of the best ones I've had the pleasure of learning from (so far).  His guidelines are clear and transparent, and he gives great feedback and advice on areas where you can improve.
